uint8_t cvmx_pki_style_parm::apad_nip

Value for WQE[APAD] when packet is not IP.

enum cvmx_pki_cache_mode cvmx_pki_style_parm::cache_mode

Select the style of write to the L2C.

0 = all packet data and next-buffer pointers are written through to memory. 1 = all packet data and next-buffer pointers are written into the cache. 2 = the first aligned cache block holding the WQE and/or front packet data are written to the L2 cache. All remaining cache blocks are not written to the L2 cache. 3 = the first two aligned cache blocks holding the WQE and front packet data are written to the L2 cache. All remaining cache blocks are not written to the L2 cache.

bool cvmx_pki_style_parm::csum_lb

Compute checksum on Layer B.

Compute checksum on Layer E.

Compute checksum on Layer F.

Compute checksum on Layer G.

uint8_t cvmx_pki_style_parm::dis_wq_dat

Separate first data buffer from the work queue entry.

0 = The packet link pointer will be at word [FIRST_SKIP] immediately followed by packet data, in the same buffer as the work queue entry. 1 = The packet link pointer will be at word [FIRST_SKIP] in a new buffer separate from the work queue entry.

bool cvmx_pki_style_parm::fcs_chk

FCS checking enabled.

bool cvmx_pki_style_parm::fcs_strip

Strip L2 FCS bytes from packet, decrease WQE[LEN] by 4 bytes.

uint16_t cvmx_pki_style_parm::first_skip

in bytes, The number of bytes from the top of the first MBUF, that the PKI stores the next pointer.

bool cvmx_pki_style_parm::force_drop

Force packet dropping.

0 = Drop packet based on PKI_AURA(0..1023)_CFG[ENA_RED/ENA_DROP]. 1 = Always drop the packet. Overrides NODROP, RAWDRP.

bool cvmx_pki_style_parm::ip6_udp_opt

IPv6/UDP checksum is optional.

IPv4 allows an optional UDP checksum by sending the all-0s patterns. IPv6 outlaws this and the spec says to always check UDP checksum. 0 = Spec compliant, do not allow optional code. 1 = Treat IPv6 as IPv4;

uint16_t cvmx_pki_style_parm::later_skip

in bytes, The number of bytes from the top of any MBUF, that is not the first MBUF that PKI writes next-pointer to.

Check if frame was received with L2 length error.

uint8_t cvmx_pki_style_parm::lenerr_eqpad

L2 length checks exact pad size.

0 = Length check uses greater then or equal comparison. 1 = Length check uses equal comparison.

bool cvmx_pki_style_parm::maxerr_en

Max frame error check enable.

uint64_t cvmx_pki_style_parm::mbuff_size

in bytes, The number of bytes to store into a buffer.

This must be even, in the range of 32 to 4096 and this must be less than or equal to the maximum size of every free page in every FPA pool this style may use.

bool cvmx_pki_style_parm::minerr_en

Min frame error check enable.

uint8_t cvmx_pki_style_parm::minmax_sel

Selects which PKI_FRM_LEN_CHK(0..1) register is used for this pkind for MINERR and MAXERR.

bool cvmx_pki_style_parm::nodrop

Disable QoS packet drop.

0 = Allowed to drop packet based on PKI_AURA(0..1023)_CFG[ENA_RED/ENA_DROP]. 1 = Never drop the packet. Overrides RAWDRP.

bool cvmx_pki_style_parm::pkt_lend

Packet little-endian.write operations of packet data to L2C to be in LE.

Base index into PKI_QPG_TBL(0..2047).

Disable computing aura by QPG algorithm.

Disable computing group by QPG algorithm.

bool cvmx_pki_style_parm::qpg_dis_grptag

Disable computing group using WQE[TAG].

1 -- Disable 0 -- Enable

bool cvmx_pki_style_parm::qpg_dis_padd

Disable computing port adder by QPG algorithm.

uint8_t cvmx_pki_style_parm::qpg_port_msb

Number of bits to shift port number in QPG.

uint8_t cvmx_pki_style_parm::qpg_port_sh

MSB to take from port number in QPG calculation 0 = Exclude port number from QPG.

4 = Include port<3:0>. 8 = Include port<7:0>.

enum cvmx_pki_qpg_qos cvmx_pki_style_parm::qpg_qos

Algorithm to select QoS field in QPG calculation.

bool cvmx_pki_style_parm::rawdrp

Allow RAW packet drop 0 = Never drop packets with WQE[RAW] set.

1 = Allow the PKI to drop RAW packets based on PKI_AURA(0..1023)_CFG[ENA_RED/ENA_DROP].

enum cvmx_sso_tag_type cvmx_pki_style_parm::tag_type

SSO tag type to schedule to.

uint8_t cvmx_pki_style_parm::wqe_hsz

Work queue header size: 0x0 = WORD0..4, standard WQE_S.

Note FIRST_SKIP may be set to not include WORD4 in memory. 0x1 = WORD0..5 0x2 = WORD0..6 0x3 = WORD0..7 else = Reserved

uint16_t cvmx_pki_style_parm::wqe_skip

in bytes, WQE start offset.

The number of bytes to skip between the buffer Pointer and WORD0 of the work-queue entry.

uint8_t cvmx_pki_style_parm::wqe_vs

Which VLAN to put into WQE[VLPTR] when VLAN stacking.

0 = Use the first (in network order) VLAN or DSA VID. 1 = Use the second (in network order) VLAN.
